race.comment: REMADOSI (5) improving mare who resumed with a slick victory over 1400m at this track in fast time. Can handle the weight rise from the inside gate. Ideally placed to feature again. SIR LUNCHALOTS (11) raced handy and pulled out plenty with a narrow win over 1300m at Wagga. Has further improvement and sure to be thereabouts. KOTAISHI (3) had to work hard early from the sticky gate with a tiring eleventh over 1400m at Albury. Gets a better set-up and assess on his good second two-back at Nowra. FIRE AND GEMSTONE (7) total forgive over the unsuitable trip with a plugging fifth over 1000m at this track. Best form is over this trip and ticks all the right boxes. LADY REVOLUTION (12) disappointed at her second run back and gets another chance in this easier contest.
